Certainly! Below is a simple HTML/CSS/JavaScript example that creates a colorful and interactive website similar to the mock-up you provided. This code will replace the joke with a random joke from a predefined list.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>My Joke Website</title>
<style>
  body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    height: 100vh;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .container {
    background-color: white;
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }
  .title {
    text-align: center;
  }
  .joke-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .joke-container .joke {
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin: 10px;
  }
  .joke-container .button {
    background-color: #007bff;
    color: white;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 10px;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .button:hover {
    background-color: #0056b3;
  }
  .button:active {
    background-color: #0056b3;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
  <div class="title">My Joke Website</div>
  <div class="joke-container">
    <div class="joke">[Funny Joke]</div>
    <div class="button">Push to reveal punchline?</div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  // Replace this with a function that fetches a random joke from a predefined list
  function getRandomJoke() {
    return "Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything!";
  }

  const button = document.querySelector('.button');
  button.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const joke = getRandomJoke();
    const jokeElement = document.querySelector('.joke');
    jokeElement.textContent = joke;
  });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

This code will create a simple webpage with a title, a joke placeholder, and a button that, when clicked, will replace the placeholder with a random joke from the `getRandomJoke` function. You can replace the `getRandomJoke` function with your own logic to fetch a joke from a predefined list or an API.

Please note that this is a very basic example and does not include any advanced features such as responsive design, accessibility, or error handling. You would need to expand upon this code to create a fully functional and polished website.
